Tesla Carview — Authors and Contributors
=========================================

Original author and copyright holder
------------------------------------
Sven Krische <it-passion@krische.com>
https://github.com/KnevS

Tesla Carview was conceived, designed and primarily implemented by
Sven Krische between 2024 and 2026. The architecture, multi-tenant
data model, Tesla Fleet API integration, virtual-key signing flow,
billing/charging-location logic, in-app handbook and the legal stack
are his original work.

The project is published under the PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0
license — see LICENSE for the full terms. The "Required Notice"
clause of that license preserves the copyright attribution above:
every copy and every derivative work must carry this notice.

Contributors
------------
Additional contributions are recorded in the git history
(git log --format='%an <%ae>' | sort -u). Human and AI-assisted
commits are both credited via standard "Co-Authored-By:" trailers.

If you submit a pull request, your contribution is licensed under
the same terms (see CONTRIBUTING.md, Developer Certificate of Origin).
